DATA CLOUD
Create a Data Cloud Sandbox (Beta)

Create a Data Cloud sandbox to use for development, testing, or training without compromising the data and applications in your production org. Data Cloud supports all the sandbox types: Developer, Developer Pro, Partial Copy, and Full Copy. Data Cloud sandboxes contain only metadata. No data is replicated when you provision Data Cloud in a sandbox, even in partial copy and full copy sandboxes.

NOTE Data Cloud in Sandbox is a pilot or beta service that is subject to the Beta Services Terms at Agreements - Salesforce.com or a written Unified Pilot Agreement if executed by Customer, and applicable terms in the Product Terms Directory. Use of this pilot or beta service is at the Customer's sole discretion. You can provide feedback and suggestions for the feature in the Trailblazer Community.

This process includes multiple steps in Data Cloud and Salesforce Platform. Bookmark () this page or keep it open in a separate window to refer to this topic.

Step 1: Opt In

Opt in to use the sandbox (beta). After you opt in, you can’t opt out.

In your production org, select Data Cloud Setup.
In the Quick Find box, enter Feature Manager, and then select Feature Manager.
In the Data Cloud In Sandbox panel, click Enable.
Step 2: Create a Sandbox
See Create a Sandbox.
Step 3: Turn On Data Cloud in the Sandbox
Log in to the sandbox.
From Data Cloud Setup, click Get Started.
Setup can take a few minutes.
Step 4: Configure the Connections

When you create a Data Cloud sandbox, connections are replicated, but the authorization data isn’t, so the connections in the sandbox org have a status of Inactive. Activate each sandbox connection, and provide the authorization information to bring data into the sandbox.

After you turn on Data Cloud, wait about 1 hour before performing this step so that the background processing can complete.

In your sandbox org, select Data Cloud Setup.
In the Quick Find box, enter Connectors, and select Connectors.
From the dropdown menu, select Activate.
Enter the authentication information for the connection, and click Save.

After you activate a connection, the data streams or other components that use the connection become active.

Step 5: Activate Data Actions and Data Action Targets

If you have data actions or data action targets in your production org, they’re replicated in a sandbox, but you must explicitly enable them.

In your sandbox, in the Data Cloud app, click Data Actions or Data Action Targets.
From the dropdown menu, select Enable.
